Quaint, but elegant - located in a pretty poppin part of Chicagoland. If you want to actually experience the Kurdish culture, by way of food, you have to get the platter that comes with the assorted accouterments. This is how breakfast is served in Iraq! Your eggs are scrambled with tomatoes, onions and peppers along with meat (go with the lamb!). Smorgasbord is the definition of an Iraqi/Kurdish breakfast, and bread is used not only for the jams, but to scoop up the eggs - like little handheld sandwiches. This is authentic, this is delicious. My wife, from Baghdad, no longer wants to eat anywhere else!! Awesome food, awesome drinks, great service, exquisite presentation.

Not all of the restaurants in Lakeview know their food, but the Gundy's (gōōndiēs) Kurdish Kitchen sure do.  Lakeview needs more restaurants like this one.  It's always a good sign when the staff know their food and line of work, and the person there really impressed me tonight with her speaking skills and delivery. She knew that menú like the back of her hand.  That's always a sign of an establishment with outstanding cuisine.  Luckily, for all of us out here in Lakeview, The Gundy's (gōōndiēs) Kurdish Kitchen has now arrived.  And it's about time.  Hopefully, I''ll see the girl I met there tonight again, although she looks and sounds like she might be on television next. I definitely think she's planning to do something like that, based on how that menú presentation and conversation went.  She's practiced that one before.  I'm wondering if she's been on the news discussing this restaurant's cuisine, or planning for it, and someone let me know if she has: because I actually don't own a television. [Delivery Review] Overall: The Gundis' great dinner experience makes me excited to try their brunch someday (and dinner again!).  The good: The chicken sac tawa was great - it had the perfect amount of spice so it wasn't too hot, and it had a nice marinade to it. The mix of charred/sauteed peppers and onions in combination with the spiced chicken gave a well-balanced flavor. Having the bulgar on top and the bread on the side was smart so neither absorbed the juices (both were also great). The portion sizes are generous as well.  The not-so-good: For a delivery option, the cost is a bit much. The ambiance of the restaurant and the freshness of the food would help justify it a little bit, but to pay almost $30 for one person is a bit much. But, it did help that I had enough leftover for lunch the next day. The delivery was also almost 45 mins late, but I don't blame that on the restaurant and rather the 3rd party app.

If you haven't been to The Gundis, you need to go! I came here for brunch recently and loved everything about this unique spot! For brunch, they offer "The Kurdish Breakfast" for 2 which includes a scramble of your choice and many sides including cheese, jams, bottomless Kurdish tea, etc for ~$40. The spread looks beautiful in pics and as tempting as this option was (mostly cause it's so pretty!) we decided to order separate items instead because we didn't care for getting a bunch of different jams, honey, olives, cucumbers, etc in place of other main dishes. They have so many good options for brunch! We ended up getting the the soft scramble with lamb ($15.95, comes with French fries), baba ganoush ($7.95), and the Kurdish bakhlawa crepes ($11.95, comes with a side of fruits). All of these dishes were wonderful! The baba ganoush was the best I've ever had. Some reviewers mentioned the bakhlawa crepes are too sweet but I didn't think so. I thought they were just the right level of sweetness and I appreciated the generous topping of pistachios sprinkled on top. Both of these were very reasonably priced. I thought the scramble was just a bit overpriced but it was a good sized portion and easily shareable between the two of us.  I also tried the Kurdish coffee which comes in the most adorable little tea cup. We also wanted to try the grilled halloumi cheese but it took some willpower to say no to this since adding this would've resulted in too much food for two people.  Some of the reviews mentioned that their dinner is pricey so not sure about that but brunch is definitely worth checking out! I had reservations for Saturday morning but even if you came without one I don't think there would be much of a wait. Which is a big plus when you're looking for a brunch spot in Chicago! Also the ambiance is pretty and service was great.

Our go to breakfast/brunch place in Chicago. The food and service is always amazing.

So happy to have the Gundi's in Lakeview. The quality of food is outstanding and very thoughtful. I am obsessed with their spicy lentil soup and love thier hommous offerings. The space is large yet warm and inviting. Ask them about the Kurdish culture and they will gladly walk you through some great history. Clark street needed a classy dining restaurant, the Gundi's has really provided that with interesting food at approachable pricing. I look forward to trying their brunch soon! Thank you Gundis.
Friendly stuff , awesome food , fairly priced
Great place and great stuff I highly recommend the breakfast great and fairly priced and next time I will try the dinner
Delicious food and salad.
I went with two others and it did not seem to have much flavor in the dishes.

I love this gem of a restaurant. warm glow of hanging lamps in a lofted space with brick walls and modern wood floors.  They have fantastic appetizers. You cannot go wrong with either the hummus or baba. Very generous portion.  Had the Chicken & Veggie Sac Tawa. Very flavorful.

The Gundis is a delicious restaurant with excellent service. Everything we had was seasoned perfectly, was bursting with flavor and all dishes were hearty and soul warming. The interior is clean and nicely decorated. The staff is willing to explain unfamiliar items. You have to eat here!!
Nice decor and location! I wish they had halal beef as well.
The best breakfast in town. Yummy egg scrambles with  fresh ingredients and lusciously spiced vegetables or sausages. The Kurdish coffee is a tasty treat. Refeshing cucumber lemonade.. go there!
What beautiful good and amazing staff
Best Kurdish food ever.
I like it !! All staff and owner they are so nice persons!

The food tastes great and of high quality. They've created some unique fusions. They offer really great service; the staff is attentive, and friendly. The ambience is really warm. Personally, I enjoy their dinner more than breakfast. Parking isn't as problematic as the rest of Lakeview.

Stuffed chicken and grilled vegetables were very good, as was the lentil soup. Kurdish tea also very good - so yeah, it is a bit pricey but the wait staff is very friendly and helpful, tables clean (restroom, too) and overall a fine dining experience.
Delicious food and such nice people. We in East Lakeview are lucky to have this place.
One of my favorite restaurants in the city, fantastic Kurdish food.  Amazingly tasty food at a fair price on top of the staff being wonderful and kind.
Great location, good food and appetizer selections, a lot of great flavors but a little pricy for this type of food. went on a non busy hour on a Friday and serivce was quick. Very friendly staff

They have an amazing brunch, and if you have two or three people split the “Kurdish Breakfast”, which comes with lots of little side dishes. Also, the people at Gundis are extremely kind and welcoming, making it a place you’ll want to come back to for sure.

Gudis is a great surprise you can get when you choose to enter that door and give Kurdish cuisine a try. Food is amazing,  great dishes presentation and the service is simply outstanding! Our server, Mauricio was very kind and attentive. Mehmet, the owner/manager/head is a remarkable human being, be sure to meet him while there. 😊😉
Delicious food.

Definitely recommendable place in Chicago if you want to have high-quality cuisine. I took a lentil soup and Mezopotamian. Both dishes topped my expectations. The waiters are professional and the atmosphere is outstanding. Deserves at least five stars.
Try the Kurdish breakfast if you're there for brunch!
Incredible food and atmosphere. A wonderful addition to the neighborhood offering a selection of food which is always delicious and filling.
They have the best breakfast of all times. Very friendly people and the place is so nice, modern and clean.
Delicious food. Good service. Tried chicken, veggie, lamb and beef dishes. All very tasty. I would absolutely come back.
Delightful delicious unusual brunch . Excellent service. There are gluten free items available. The background music was classical jazz perfect for occasion. Highly recommend.
Absolutely fantastic! The food is amazing and the service was great. I will definitely be coming back and I recommend it to everyone.
Great tasty food, authentic local food and dessert
Turkish breakfast for 2 is amazing, grab a friend and go!
Great food and service
The food, ambiance and decor are all top notch. The Kurdish coffee and tea were both delicious. Will definitely be coming back.

Went here on a Sunday night. The restaurant was more then half empty yet the hostess tried to seat us at a very small side table next to a noisy bunch. I asked for a different table and was told they were all reserved. Yeah right ... total nonsense she just wanted to be rude. We left. Not coming back here.
Delicious food, decent portions, friendly staff. Looked like it was recently renovated, the front is all windows so you can people watch galore if you get bored. It's pretty lively place.
Great place for brunch! We'll be back.

If you are in the area TRY this place! Food and service was amazing. We had the sample from the app side... the Baba ghanouj was the best part. We also got the grill calamari which I recommend and I also recommend taking the bread and dipping it into the sauce... yummy! I got the mardin lamb special. It was okay the 2 sauces worked well together, however 2 of my friends got the lamb shanks, that was the best pick. The lamb was just so fall of the bone and the favors were on point. Definitely do dessert and the Kurdish coffee. The Kurdish coffee was creamy and sweet (a good balance of sweet and not over powering sweet). We got the dark chocolate mousse with Pomegranate drizzle... just get it. If you like dark chocolate you will be in heaven. It’s a good size you can share with 2-3 peeps if you are just looking for a little bit of dessert. Overall this is a great like gem in lakeview! We will visit again to brunch.
Get the Kurdish breakfast for two! So delish...no wait and so much for the money :).
It's when nice atmosphere and great people meet with delicious food...
I felt the love in each ingredient, I loved the food here
Generous portions, delicious and interesting food and great service.
Amazing food and service.
The lamb with eggplant was disappointing (overcooked lamb). Every Middle Eastern restaurant should be lamb experts. The grilled octopus was excellent as the service!
Excellent food and service. Salads fresh and delicious. Meat perfect!!

Amazing food and super nice atmosphere! The waiters are super nice and will never let you run out of water or wait too long for your food. Speaking of the food, everything we tried was amazing and very fresh! The Kurdish coffee is a must!
Good food Great Baklava I hope they survive This is a place that I enjoy but for most locals and middel eastern patrons large portion is important  The chef has great taste  I will come back
Fresh Kurdish dishes!!!
Excellent food and service!
This is an awesome place and one of the best restaurants I have been to in Lake View. The appetizer sampler for dinner was one of the highlights, and everyone in my party really enjoyed their meal.
Food was awesome and the servers were wonderful!  My only complaint is the noise level, which left me hoarse from having to shout to converse.
Good food
Rip off of Turkish food
The food was quite good and the servers were attentive.
(Translated by Google) Very good place, exquisite food !!  (Original) Muy buen lugar, comida exquisita!!
Excellent food and wine, If you go to Chicago you must visit it.
(Translated by Google) Mardin Lamb Stew one of the best I've ever had  (Original) Mardin Lamb Stew de lo mejor que he probado

Great Kurdish restaurant. Came all the way from los angeles to chicago and during my chucago visit i went this nice restaurant. Ordered soujuck eggs which was delicious. Service was amazing. Metered Parking is awailable at front. Clean restrooms.
Good value and homemade feel & taste. I most enjoyed the lentil soup with goat cheese

I loved there breakfast for two. We also got and omelette. There were 3 of us, and honestly the breakfast for 2 would have been enough, but the omelette was just as impressive as good. The seats toward the front are the best for people watching with the large windows.

LOVED this place. Atmosphere good. Food magnificent. Wonderful service. A bit pricey but worth it. Some of the best food I have tasted any where. Great job with gluten free items. We had a wonderful time... Even with a 3 year old... He behaved nicely as well. They were great with him. Oh and try a cup of the Kurdish coffee. I don't like coffee. My husband got it...I tasted it and well... He had to order another cup. 😉 Will go back again when we are back in town...it woul be on my to-do and enjoy list.

My favorite breakfast place in Chicago their scrambled eggs with lamb, peppers and tomatoes is dreamy. Try the Kurdish breakfast for two we will totally love all the side dishes of come with it and bottomless Kurdish tea.
Fabulous food and excellent service.  This is my new favorite restaurant.

I always go to Gundis. Because the foods and desserts really good and the waiters are really nice people. Today, I went to Gundus with my guest. During our dinner, waiters was so interested. But, we have finished desserts yet and I was still drinking my tea one of the waiters that brought check. And I said we didn’t want check, he said you’ve sat too long. 2 hours and we’ve finished yet!! What a rude! The other waiters were really good. He should be a gentle person. I am customer. Do you do this behaviour to Only Turkish people???
Fantastic meal!   Very friendly and helpful service too. Definitely make a reservation if you're dining at a peak hour.

Good atmosphere. Super friendly wait staff.  I had pieces of grilled lamb atop of bed of pureed zucchini.  It was excellent.  But this stuffed roast chicken breast and pasta dish that were delivered to the table were not quite that level in my opinion. I would say it's definitely worth a try.
Great customers service and very lovely people super clean .did not care to much about the spicess they used but was spicy .

Excellent menu Items for all different pallets Tasty appetizers..succulent entrees... Tea lovers have to try the traditional tea The cucumber lemonade a must as well.. The staff courteous and knowledgeable about the menu.. Give the traditional items a try if you need to play it safe... But trust nothing will disappoint on this menu🎉 Enjoy 🎉🎉
Amazing food - fresh and healthy and flavorful
Really good place and service. The red lentil soup is awesome.
The food is amazing - fresh and delicious - and the service is over the top. We love their Kurdish Breakfast and brunch and dinner is delicious too! A definite must try!

Exceptional service and food. Everything I ordered was beyond delicious.. All types of bread they use for the Sampler is quality and very flavorful. The main dish that anyone who come here should try is their Stuff Chicken Breast. Also, the aromatic Kurdish tea and Rice Pudding is a must-try when it comes to dessert. Service is exceptional. The staff made sure you have everything ready and they are always there to make sure that your food is going right. The downside would be the price, but given that it is the only-Kurdish restaurant in town and its exceptionally tasty dishes, How can I deny going back there!
Great brunch place! Good service, great food and decent prices.
Amazing brunch, wonderful service, clean bathroom, relaxing ambiance!  This place has everything.  Thank you for a wonderful meal!
Huge experience... The Kurdish emperience is definitely for 2+ ! The sujuk omelette will stick in my mind for all the right reasons. :)
Great food specially breakfast.

A welcome addition to the somewhat stale South Lakeview dining scene. The staff was so sweet and welcoming and the cuisine, while not groundbreaking, is fresh and well prepared. The lamb and eggplant stew was delicious.
Outstanding place! Excellent food and great service. I mentioned my birthday on my reservation and they brought a little cake with a candle, free of charge. :D

Truly outstanding food. I had the Zaza pasta and it was stunningly delicious. My friend had a scramble that she also really liked. The side of olives was ample. Service was attentive but not intrusive. Beer was very cold. Interior is clean, simple, attractive. I recommend this place without reservation.
Great experience! We loved the place. It is really friendly , clean and nice place. Great service. The food was really good😍  best brunch experience in Chicago!  Kids loved it,too

I went in the morning and had the Kurdish breakfast with tea, it was very delicious, And more than enough for two people. They also sever tea non stop. I like the bread and sides. They also said that they offer halal zabiha meat. Also the staff were very nice. Overall very fancy place worth the visit.

I’m traveling from NY and we happened to come across this place for brunch. What and incredible and unique experience! Definitely recommend getting the Kurdish Breakfast with Soujok (sausage). It’s a high quality, diverse and delicious arrangement of jams, cheese, soft scramble and a LOT of other things! And service was excellent they kept the tea cups full and the fresh bread coming without ever asking once! Would definitely recommend!
Try the Kurdish Coffee!
One of the best meals I’ve had in Chicago. Fantastic Vegetarian options. Get the halloumi!
Food is delicious. Service great.
Very nice. Delicious food. Fancier Middle Eastern. Wine was amazing.
Super food, fantastic service....
Absolutely delicious!!

Our first time with the family, we had the best Adana Kebap. The server Mehmet was very attentive and friendly. He immediately spoke to us in Turkish. They have a wide variety of selection ranging from vegetarian to sea food, and all sounded delicious. We will definitely come back to the Gundis to taste the rest of the flavors!
Had the spicy red lentil soup and beet salad. Both were delicious and served with great customer service. Nice atmosphere with music to compliment the ambiance.
We had the chicken pasta, lamb scramble, apple pancake, and a wrap. Everything was delicious. I'll be back.
Absolutely amazing.  From staff to food.  A great experience to enjoy in chicago.   I'll be coming back every trip.   Kurdish coffee was the best coffee I've ever had.
Their food is amazing and the staff was kind and polite! Loves it

Probably best new brunch I've had this year. The breakfast platter for two comes with delicious jams and honey not to mention the delicious egg dish. All the food was amazing. The meal took a while so be prepared to not rush.  Everyone who worked there was friendly and very helpful.

This restaurant is great.  We were a party of 10 and ordered the mixed starter plate and the halloumi salad, we, liked it so much and ordered another round.  We then proceeded with an entree for each.  I had the stuffed chicken, it was super delicious. We also had the salmon, lamb shank and shrimp.  Everything we had was delicious.  Finished with a nice mix of desserts, all were very good.  Will return.

They are so generous and kind. We came last minute for Mother's day and they made a special place just for us, even though they were full with reserved tables. The food was beyond amazing in itself, but it was their hospitality that really won us over. And they had Tulips for all the mother who came! Just lovely!
Very delicious but lil expansive
New neighborhood find in Lincoln Park, adventure in need and different cusine and spices. Very friendly professional staff.

I was pleasantly surprised by Gundis. The Beet Salad was fantastic! The rest of our food was really good too. We had the apricot rice pudding and it was delicious as well. The interior is simple and comfortable. The wait staff was nice and accommodating.  I would definitely recommend if you are in the area.
We went for brunch... Was really good... All the waiters are so nice and friendly! I loved this place.
Tasty food and helpful service.
Delicious and great service!  Will definitely go back!

Visited for the first time not really knowing what to expect but the food was excellent, our server very attentive and friendly. He took our coffee at the end of the meal and read our “fortunes” in the cups. Made for fun conversation afterward. Will definitely be back.

Outstanding service coupled with equally good food help this Kurdish restaurant make it a worthwhile stop for anyone craving some Kurdish cuisine.  Especially tasty are the brunch dishes.  Eggs with sujuk (beef sausage), vegetables and some especially delicious potato "sticks" are worth getting up early to beat the rush on a Saturday or Sunday!

We had a very elegant and delicious breakfast. Authentic please remind me my hometown Mus in Turkey . One of the best places I have ever seen in entire United States. I would recommend everybody who wants  have  unique taste of Kurdish and Turkish Kitchen mixture. I’m so happy and pleased with servers and foods. Thanks The Gundi’s to provide us a perfect and peaceful day.
Service, food and atmosphere were great.

I had a wonderful lunch here with friends last week. The food was outstanding - light, healthy and delicious, especially the spicy red lentil soup, the creative salads, baklava, tart cucumber lemonade and homemade wheat bread. I would come back to try the abundant Kurdish breakfast. Service was charming and professional and the atmosphere is bright and stylish. I will definitely be back!

Second time for brunch and will be back again. Wonderful, friendly service and food. Kurdish tea also makes me happy and comes with an incredible brunch sharing option for two.  A friend has Celiac and gluten intolerance and these are easily handled by the invested owners. I appreciate the thought they put into their Customers.
Good food and nice staff
This is my favorite restaurant in Chicago. Clean and healthy food that taste amazing. Also a great spot to take a date.
Friendly and excellent service and delicious food, thank you! We will definitely be back for dinner to try the rest of the menu!

Went for lunch.  Wanted to go for dinner with the whole menu.  Had the wrap and fries along with the hummus.  Very good and you can tell very fresh.  Waiter was great and overall atmosphere was nice.  A $25 lunch is pushing it and would come for dinner but for that price at lunch.....I don't know
Great brunch with great people!
Staff so friendly and food was great. Highly recommend it!  P.S. Order Adana Kebab it’s delicious
I enjoyed there. Food service I wish they would have more liquor options

Amazing brunch and service. Definetly want to come back for the shared options. Seems to be a place where sitting, taking your time and slowly drinking tea over conversation is encouraged along side the large shared meals.
I had already dug into this anazing sampler, then thought, this is worthy of a picture. It really was a great find, not that expensive for the location and excellent food.

I’ve been here for both brunch and dinner. Both are in fierce competition. If you’re going for brunch, get a few dishes to share. Most of the dishes are savory and honestly pretty reasonable. The outstanding services also complements every meal. Will be back!
Excellent fresh food.  I didn't know what to expect and the meals were great.  Kinda loud however.  Lunch was empty a dinner I'd recommend reservations or go early.
Always a beautiful meal and warm hospitality.
One of the best restaurants for Middle Eastern cuisine. I would recommend everyone to try the Kurdish coffee (warning, it contains pistachios)! The sac tava is one of my favorites.
Beef Shish is amazing, the sampler appetizer was also good.
The breakfast for two is a top breakfast experience in Chicago
Food is unbelievably fresh and tasty. Can’t say enough good things about the staff here as well, so kind and attentive.

Loved this little spot! It's nice for a special occasion, my first time having Kurdish food and it was delicious. I have to say though, it is a bit pricey ($130 for 2 people after tax+tip) and it's pretty loud in the restaurant. The apps and entree we're delivered with little wait time, but the dessert took about 25min. The waiters were very helpful pointing out GF options. Overall a great experience, highly recommend!
Excellent food and service. The sampler is divine. Definitely coming back!
Excellent dining, great Middle Eastern Kabobs, prepared in authentic Kurdish style.
Good authentic food

Very good food and lovely atmosphere! Kurdish coffee with a taste of roasted pistachios -- very special indeed. Not too sweet baklava with fig in center beautifully presented deserves a favorable mention. The starter sampler is highly recommended - such fine tastes!

Amazing Kurdish food!!!  Came here for a brunch. Had sujuk (halal beef sausage) omelet and the Wayne spicy spinach omelet. Both served with freshly baked whole wheat bread, olives and house fries. Everything was so tasty.. We ordered Kurdish tea (which is the same as Arabic/Turkish/Persian black tea) and it was so good. Personally, next time I would get only the bread with their BLACK olives (green olives were just OK here), house cheese and tea. It is definitely not your typical regular brunch.  Olives Olives are sacred to me. They burst in vitamins, righteous lipids, essential minerals, significant iron, antioxidants/oleic acid (protects against aging, dementia and wrinkles).  And they're so tasty with hot black tea like the one served here.. You should eat at least 1 olive a day..  Atmosphere Classic, clean and standard place. Parking was a piece of cake, but it was a snowy super bowl Sunday!. Love the snow fall outside while enjoying a hot cup of tea inside.  Staff and service Professional and friendly. Prices are very reasonable.  If you're looking for a healthy, tasty, out-of-routine weekend brunch, The Gundis is a lovely option. Remember to get the black tea and the black olives. And read my lecture about the importance of olives as above..
Everything was great.  Loved the food and staff.  Nice atmosphere.  Mehmet is a great and friendly server.  5 🌟!
Solid brunch
Amazing experience..food was outstanding..service was attentive but not obtrusive..moved to number one on my list

Went for the Kurdish breakfast tofu scramble which serves a lot of food for two people. Service is spotty and waited a long time for our food. Staff is extremely friendly. They just need to work on their service. restaurant is very spacious and not too crowded for brunch time.
Very good innovative unique food at the only Kurdish restaurant in the area. This place is very popular. It has been featured on TV shows such as Check Please! Reservations are recommended.
